
                =============================
                =  How to build primesieve  =
                =============================


Unix-like operating systems
===========================

Open a terminal and `cd' into the primesieve directory,
then run the following commands:

$ ./configure
$ make
$ make install

Microsoft Windows
=================

Open a Visual Studio Command Prompt and `cd' into the primesieve
directory, then run the following command:

> nmake -f Makefile.msvc

primesieve console application
==============================

The primesieve console (terminal) application can generate primes
and prime k-tuplets up to 2^64 using multiple threads.

Usage examples:

$ ./primesieve 10000           Count the primes below 10000
$ ./primesieve 10000 -p1       Print the primes below 10000
$ ./primesieve 1e5 2e5 -p2     Print the twin primes within [10^5, 2*10^5]
$ ./primesieve --help          Print the help menu

